  "text": "Django's admin filter rendering pipeline determines whether to display filters through a multi-stage filtering process:\n\n1. **Base Filter Class (ListFilter)**: Located in `django/contrib/admin/filters.py` at line 26, the `ListFilter` class defines an abstract `has_output()` method (lines 41-47) that all filter subclasses must implement. This method determines whether a filter should be displayed in the sidebar.\n\n2. **Field-Based Filters (FieldListFilter)**: At line 171 of `django/contrib/admin/filters.py`, the `FieldListFilter` class provides a base implementation for field-specific filters. Its `has_output()` method (lines 188-189) always returns `True`, indicating that field filters should always be displayed if they have choices.\n\n3. **Related Field Filters (RelatedFieldListFilter)**: The specialized `RelatedFieldListFilter` class is defined at line 222 of `django/contrib/admin/filters.py`. It overrides `has_output()` (lines 248-253) with custom logic that returns `True` only if the number of lookup choices plus any empty choice option exceeds 1. This prevents empty related-field filters from displaying.\n\n4. **ChangeList Filter Collection (ChangeList.get_filters)**: In `django/contrib/admin/views/main.py`, the `ChangeList` class (line 67) implements the `get_filters()` method (starting at line 175) which:\n   - Instantiates each configured list filter\n   - Calls `spec.has_output()` on each filter spec at line 221\n   - Only includes filters in `filter_specs` if they pass the `has_output()` check (line 222)\n\n5. **Filter Specs Assignment (ChangeList.get_queryset)**: The `get_queryset()` method (line 527) unpacks the results from `get_filters()` and assigns `self.filter_specs` at line 530, storing only the filters that returned `True` from `has_output()`.\n\n6. **Template Rendering**: The template tag `admin_list_filter` in `django/contrib/admin/templatetags/admin_list.py` (line 521) renders individual filter specs by calling `spec.choices(cl)` and rendering the template.\n\n7. **Template Iteration**: In `django/contrib/admin/templates/admin/change_list.html` at line 72, the template iterates over `cl.filter_specs` and calls `{% admin_list_filter cl spec %}` for each filter.\n\nThe key control point for filter visibility is the `has_output()` method. For `RelatedFieldListFilter`, empty related-field filters are excluded because the method checks if there are sufficient choices (more than 1 after accounting for the empty choice option)."
}

